eNCA’s senior journalist Aviwe Mtila is in CapeTown and had a look at the situation on the ground. #eNCA #DStv403  CAPE TOWN - In December last year, the Western Cape education department said it had made progress in placing learners in schools ahead of the 2023 school year. Now, as coastal schools reopen on Wednesday, it's clear that not all children have been placed, with snaking queues in some district offices. eNCA’s senior journalist Aviwe Mtila has the details in the video above.